reports.title: The Overview Dashboard
reports.query:
Below is a graph conataining all the tags and problems:
- Tags: purple nodes
- Problems: finished problems in red, unfinished ones in yellow
- Relationships: SIMILAR_TO, BELONGS_TO

reports.title: Graph of all problems and tags
Tags
reports.query: match (n:Tag) return n.title as Title, n.uri as URL

reports.title: Recommendation by difficulty levels
reports.query:
match (n:Problem)-[r]-(s)
where n.uri in
['https://leetcode.com/problems/check-if-every-row-and-column-contains-all-numbers/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/merge-two-sorted-lists/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/find-all-k-distant-indices-in-an-array/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-product-subarray/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/find-the-duplicate-number/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/jump-game-viii/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/shortest-palindrome/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/non-negative-integers-without-consecutive-ones/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-number-of-non-overlapping-palindrome-substrings/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/reverse-nodes-in-k-group/']


return n, r, s

reports.title: Problems to do
reports.query:
match (n:Problem)
where n.uri in
['https://leetcode.com/problems/check-if-every-row-and-column-contains-all-numbers/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/merge-two-sorted-lists/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/find-all-k-distant-indices-in-an-array/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-product-subarray/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/find-the-duplicate-number/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/jump-game-viii/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/shortest-palindrome/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/non-negative-integers-without-consecutive-ones/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-number-of-non-overlapping-palindrome-substrings/', 'https://leetcode.com/problems/reverse-nodes-in-k-group/']

return n.title as Title,
n.difficulty as Difficulty, n.acceptance as Acceptance

reports.title: Breakdown by difficulty levels
reports.query:
match (n:Problem{finished:"Done"})
with n
//match (n {difficulty: "Hard"})
return count(n) as Hard, n.difficulty as Difficulty

reports.title: Finished
reports.query:
match (n:Problem{finished:"Done"})
with n
//match (n {difficulty: "Hard"})
return count(n) as Hard, n.difficulty as Difficulty
